cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about analyzing the learned internal representations in an end-to-end ASR model, which involves natural language processing and speech recognition.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with acoustic features and phonetic representations in speech recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks in end-to-end ASR systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with the use of neural networks for speech recognition, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the analysis of learned representations in a network.
